Slots
-----
1) main event
Next to the one time event, there is a button called slot
Opens a new slots wizard (calendar view - dragable element, and you can add slots)
The main event editor, just show the slots in read only form, maybe scrolabble (undecided)
(The slot wizard maybe only for public and friends event)
Naturally the frequency affects the slot what you can add - monthly - you can pick some days, but on daily not.
2) request to join on event explore (you can fully book an event - a flag on main event, but in this case the request to join is a "book")
when you request join slots vizard in read only form popups up and you can choose a slot
(the request join menu itself should show red counter or different way that you need to choose from slots)
3) slots has separate and coloured chat channels

Ratings
-------
separated friends, you met with both, but they didn't meet with each other
friends in common, when you didn't met with someone, but you both meet a person, who meet with both of you

1) home
next to single mode/pair mode -> trasform to dropdown box, add "separated friends" / "friends in common"
separated friends is a pair rate view, but two auto completer textbox at top of the image (you can put event/friends name etc.)
the filtered list can be vertically scrollable on the pair panel the two people independently
2) actitivies - rating
separated friends -> on your side -> pair rate - given / on other side -> pair rate received (and it's friendss in common actually)
next to pair rate label (dropdown box/mobile menu sheet) you can set - social badge on/off -
so it's filtering the separated/friends in common from the given/received list
when switch on the given/received red counter applies

Asset explore
-------------
You can borrow items from a foreigner (assets (accomodation/car/suplies) with public or friends visibility)
Assets can be filtered by capacity, availability, topic (very similar screen then the event explore)
Assets can have price tag (we haven't introduced purse for public/frineds event also)

